> Thanks for the report! I can take a look at that logic, as it could likely benefit from being more atomic anyway, but looking at your callstack, it's a bit odd. There shouldn't be anything that can go from `DataRequest._response` to `DownloadRequest.downladTask` to `DataRequest.dataTask`. Do you have any more traces I can see? (No need for screen shots, you can copy / paste the content.)

@jshier Yeah that part was really weird for me too. I can't find more traces at the moment. If I notice it again, I will post the stack trace. For this kind of impossible stack trace, could it be a bug with Xcode symbolicating the crash? Or there's some memory corruption going on? If there's some memory corruption and the app was already in an undefined state, then I guess this is not really the fault of Alamofire library.
I don't see any other similar issue posted. So if you do a logic check and can't find anything, maybe it is some other issue. In that case... maybe just close the ticket.
